{% extends 'base.html.jinja' %}
{% block title %} Advent of code 2025 - Utils {% endblock %}
{% block js_and_css %}
{% endblock %}
{% block content %}
<div class="container-fluid">
    {% include 'intro.html.jinja' %}
    {% with day_number=day_index %}
    {% include 'nav.html.jinja' %}
    {% endwith %}
    <div class="container border border-dark border-4 rounded-3 my-4">
      <h2 class="mt-2">Presentation</h2>
      <p>
        The purpose of this site is to showcase my
        <a href="https://adventofcode.com/">Advent of Code 2025</a>
        project. The entire site is static and built without JavaScript, using
        only client-side Python thanks to
        <a href="https://pyscript.net/">PyScript</a>. This framework allows
        Python code to be executed in the browser via
        <a href="https://webassembly.org/">WebAssembly (WASM)</a>
        , offering an alternative to JavaScript. Each puzzle is therefore
        solved and displayed using Python executed locally in your browser.
      </p>
      <p>
        An anti-spoiler tagging system allows you to navigate without the risk
        of inadvertently discovering solutions.
      </p>
      <p>Feel free to explore the different solutions on offer.</p>
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
